INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (1,1,1,'Welcome on brand new nB) website !','\n            <p>\n                    <strong>Welcome on our new website !</strong>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                    Nuit Blanche is quite an old team. We are playing like crazy since 1996 and let\'s guess we are geek enough to continue to play for decades.\n                    Since 1996, we made MANY websites. Four versions with various success were made on the collector url <em>clannb.quakexpert.com</em>. Then when StarCraft 2 opened, we quickly created a small website\n                    on <em>egame-star</em>.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                    But none of them was good enough for our exceptionnal team !<br />\n                    So I decided to build a brand new one based on new powerful tools : Symfony 2, Doctrine 2 with some extra magical dust.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                    Here is a list of functions i hope you\'ll enjoy :\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n                    <li>leagues and seasons recaps</li>\n                    <li>detailled clan war page with related replays</li>\n                    <li>detailled profiles with statistics, clan war games and replays related</li>\n                    <li>cute replay page with apm chart, chat log and more</li>\n                    <li>embedded stream pages, with live stream, show history, ...</li>\n                    <li>... and more you\'ll discover while browsing this website</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n                    But we are still in a <strong>v0.9 beta version</strong> !<br />\n                    Until the end of the summer, I\'ll add more cool stuff :\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n                    <li>forum</li>\n                    <li>replay notes and comments</li>\n                    <li>internationalization for french only speakers (they suck I know !)</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n                    So..... I really hope you\'ll enjoy that shit and that you\'ll help us making it an active website.<br />\n                    <em>Stay tuned</em>,<br />\n                    AlepH\n            </p>\n        ','2011-05-30 14:59:55'),(2,2,1,'Pandaria nB vs AdC','Here is the result of last pandaria clanwar :\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:39}</div>\r\n\r\n<p>It was a mannered clanwar but quite long to organize, all the nB players managed to win their 1v1 even if tartiflette wanted to make some suspense.\r\nA special congratulations to sweety for his first win in 1v1 pandaria and to our really nice \"subsitute\" 2v2 team: tartiflette + sweety.</p>\r\n\r\nGG all and see you next week for another pandaria war!','2011-06-02 13:36:34'),(3,2,1,'A new challenge for nB) team : pgleague','Finally the divisions came up and i let you see where we are:\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/570420pgleague.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see , we are in first division and i\'m gonna do a small presentation of the teams here :</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://uppix.net/b/f/8/9b90e0d1798e60e419d001dba94b4.png\" alt=\"\" /><h3>EXTENSIVE TEAM</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A good team from the first division of pandaria league, they have good players such as Master(bouh you\'re noob!), Syde or even Vinceee . Even if they are not in the first teams on pandaria, no doubt they will be hard to beat . One of the favorite teams to my mind.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/_PTnlJNSPl0g/TbqF3WB3coI/AAAAAAAAAK4/jImZfzcV1Jg/logo_bl\" alt=\"\" /><h3>BLAST TEAM</h3>\r\n<p>Another good team from the D1 of pandaria with indy, shadox, it\'s a pretty stable team which is here from the beginning, that\'s to say they have a good experience of high level. Another strong team of the division.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/206058soleilnoir.gif\" alt=\"\" /><h3>SOLEIL NOIR</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is the dark side of Nuit Blanche, that gay of haddes decided to build a team as strong as us and i must admit he managed to do it .Izno, renzan are the center of their success even if some others are more and more efficient : Bomber, and above all Metzi. With their powerful 2v2 Team, it will be a hard clanwar .</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.sas-team.net/download/file.php?avatar=2_1218638992.gif\" alt=\"\" /><h3>Soul And Serenity</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>First of the D3 pandaria league with 6 points more than us, they\'re the only team which was able to beat us . So i won\'t do any useless comment, they have a strong team (rasmuth lost 0-2 fast) and a good 2v2 as well, it\'s another solid team.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.clan-cst.com/logo/logo-cst_100px_square.png\" alt=\"\" /><h3>CsT</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another team from the D1 pandaria league, even if they\'ll probable go to D2, it remains a good team which has lost, it\'s true, some members like Eeel .</p>\r\n\r\nFinally , all the clanwars will be difficult and it will be a good test for our team, i have special hopes for that league, especially for players like Bouh who begins to manage his PvT match up, even if it\'s still hard for him.\r\nSweety who showes a great motivation for the competition and the ladder . Pepem who continues his winning streak on pandaria league and finally Rasmuth, a strong asset of our team.\r\nAnd i finish with our 2v2 team : sweety and tartiflette who use their brain (one for both!) to win some impossible 2v2 !! Keep on that way guys and let\'s wish us some luck for that competition. I add that aleph will probably admin that league to help me.','2011-06-02 14:12:01'),(4,1,1,'Website\'s evolution','<p>\r\nYou\'ll find <a href=\"http://www.clan-nuitblanche.org/to_come\">there</a> the list of the next stuff to be developped. <strong>Feel free to mail me if you wanna add any idea !</strong>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>\r\nI would really like to thank you all for you activity on it.\r\nFor the first 5 days it\'s :\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>100 different visitors for 300 total visits</li>\r\n<li>and 2209 pages viewed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nThe 3 most viewed pages are the team list, replay list and stream page and i\'ll just let you guess which player profile is the most visited : p\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAnyway, i hope you\'ll continue to make this website very active. DO NOT hesitate to add replay and to make live streams, i\'ll add the forum really soon to get more \"community stuff\".\r\n</p>\r\nCheers,<br />\r\nAlepH','2011-06-04 11:23:39'),(5,1,1,'Next week-end wars','<p>\r\nClan Wars of this week aren\'t finished yet but both of them are already won thanks to a 3-0 score. Let\'s hope we\'ll add the 2 remaining points to get 3 \"5-0\" wars in a row :p\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI just wanted to inform you that next week there\'ll be no less than 3 wars for PGL, SC2CL and Pandaria !!!\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>date TDB</strong> \r\nWe\'ll have to face <strong><img src=\"http://www.clan-nuitblanche.org/bundles/ihqsnuitblanche/images/flags/fr.gif\" alt=\"\" /> AS</strong> for Pandaria  : we must win this war by this largest margin possible to get to upper division.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>date TDB</strong> For PGLeague we\'ll face <strong><img src=\"http://www.clan-nuitblanche.org/bundles/ihqsnuitblanche/images/flags/fr.gif\" alt=\"\" /> BLAST</strong>. Difficult and exciting clan war versus good players (GGs, ShadOx and more).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sunday 12th, 19:00</strong> I\'ll be admin for the SC2CL war versus <strong><img src=\"http://www.clan-nuitblanche.org/bundles/ihqsnuitblanche/images/flags/ru.gif\" alt=\"\" /> SCB</strong>. As we can\'t except anything for this SC2CL season anymore, i\'ll try to make play the ones who wanna train a bit and play more wars. So just ask me here or on the forum if you wanna play it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nTraining everyone, lot of wars until a very calm summer. But if you wanna make some lan events in july or august, you\'d better win those wars : DD\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nStay Tuned !\r\n</p>','2011-06-07 10:27:03'),(6,2,1,'Pandaria nB vs SkG','<p><h3><img src=\"http://oospores.net/nuitblanche/logo_100_100.png\" alt=\"\" />  VS     <img src=\"http://www.sakge-gaming.com/Sponsors/pandaria.png\" alt=\"\" /></h3>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We finally come to the end of that season, only one clanwar left after that one and we\'ll know if we access the playoff.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:42}</div>\r\n\r\nA really nice result from our team, especially in the 1v1.\r\nRasmuth managed to defeat a nice Z , with a special mention on the second game (only stalkers ... grrr!!!)\r\nBouh won 2-1 vs the imba race vs him: T , i must admit i feared in last game since tendian used to attack much on one base, which seemed to represent a problem for bouh.\r\n\r\nPepem won with the same score, he could have won 2-0 if zirplay hadn\'t made some gay DTs and sweety won easily.\r\n\r\n<p><strong>But the unbelievable thing is that sweety and tartiflette lost a 2v2 </p>\r\n</strong> <img src=\"http://www.madeinlens.com/forum/public/style_emoticons/default/whatlu1.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>That means we mustn\'t do any mistake for next clanwars vs As.</p>\r\n\r\nThanks to all players who were there to play or obs the games and gg for the win.','2011-06-08 00:18:35'),(7,2,1,'PGLEAGUE DAY 1 : nB vs SaS','<p><h3><img src=\"http://oospores.net/nuitblanche/logo_100_100.png\" alt=\"\" />   VS <img src=\"http://www.sas-team.net/download/file.php?avatar=2_1218638992.gif\" alt=\"\" /></h3></p>\r\n\r\nA really nice clanwar in which we had to take our revenge vs the SaS team. In fact we lost the last war vs SaS in pandaria and we had to show other face in competition vs that team.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:46}</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A really nice war from nB especially in the 1v1 , indeed, every player succeeded in winning their 1v1 and many with a large score:\r\n\r\nSweety  managed to win Urice 2-0 and took  his revenge on the pandaria war.\r\nMuth defeated the good T PcK with the same score.\r\nPepem won his match 2-0 as well as Bouh.\r\n\r\nReally gg for that </p>\r\n\r\n<p> UNFORTUNATELY, once again , sweety and tartiflette lost the 2V2 in a 0-2 score </p> \r\n<img src=\"http://www.madeinlens.com/forum/public/style_emoticons/default/rbgxzn.gif\" alt=\"\" />','2011-06-08 23:55:05'),(8,2,1,'Welcome to Pocket!','<h3><img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/524394here.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>I\'m glad to welcome <strong>Pocket</strong> in our roster . He\'s a really talented Terran player from broodwar.\r\nHe played in the France Team for 1v1 and 2v2 even if he was more specialized in the 22 at the end of the game. \r\n\r\nFirst of all he will be part of our 2v2 team with pepem, and they both succeeded in leading their Master division within 2 days.\r\n</p>\r\n<p> After that, i was told he would maybe play again 1v1, if that\'s the case, he will be a really important part of the line up for 1v1 or for 2v2 . </p>\r\nWelcome to nB) Family Gianni !\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/422696perfs.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','2011-06-10 23:51:39'),(9,2,1,'Ases Cup tourney !','<h3><img src=\"http://www.wannawar.com/_img_tournoi/moyen/20110314000357_33_imgprinc_20110120210105_23_imgprinc_ases.png\" alt=\"\" /></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><h3><strong>SUNDAY 9PM</strong></h3>\r\n<p> This tourney is open to <strong>anybody</strong> \r\nIt\'s a 1v1 tourney with Bo1 until 1/4 finals where it will be BO3.\r\nThis tourney is first of all a way to have fun , the winner will have the opportunity to play a BO3 vs Adel and will be able to win a videogame in the list : </p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/618610jeux.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I forgot to mention that the final bo3 vs adel will be streamed on the webtv of AS team. Don\'t hesitate to subscribe, if some nB do , plz post it as a comment so we can follow your evolution in the tourney, hf all.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> There are the rules of the tourney (in french)</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://img4.hostingpics.net/pics/641607rules.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p><strong>Link to tourney:</strong><a href=\"http://www.wannawar.com/tournoi-starcraft-2/2945/detail/ases-cup-parraine-par-met450adel-14.html\">ASES TOURNEY</a>','2011-06-11 14:24:23'),(10,2,1,'The ACTIVE team','<p>What is being active in the team ?\r\n\r\n- Being here on the channel and active in discussions\r\n- Making CG games and/or ladder .\r\n- Get involved in the life of the team : forum/channels/ take part to wars.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn order for the team not to be full of ghosts and to free some active slots in the roster , here is a sum up of the ACTIVE members of the team:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/769282oldies.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\nYopYop (P)\r\nRaptors (P)\r\nLapin (P)\r\nHammer (random)\r\nBaghla (T)\r\nAcid (P)\r\nnBSpoon (P)\r\nCloon (P)\r\nSchoua ( P)\r\nWhiteman (z)\r\nSwarm (T)\r\nALundra(z)\r\nswarm(t)\r\nwhiteman(z)\r\nnaudar (r)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those members are all inactive or can\'t take part to major activity of the team. That\'s why they were put as oldies. It is up to any of thoses players to show more activity and to be accepted again in the active roster. For example, Lio was moved again to active section thanks to his presence in the channel and his cgs.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-tVE8oHg4ad8/TWN3FPTtTHI/AAAAAAAAD2M/4K1Nu5GyIqA/s1600/fcys14-tux-militaire-1696.png\" alt=\"\" /><h3>ACTIVE TEAM:15</h3></p>\r\n\r\nSweety (P)\r\nHeero ( Z)\r\nTartiflette (T)\r\nMttn (T)\r\nHane (P)\r\nBeerwithme( Z)\r\nBouh (P)\r\nPepem (Z)\r\nMyst (R)\r\nIcedice (P)\r\nLoveeyes (T)\r\nRasmuth( P)\r\nSangui ( Z)\r\nkura(T)\r\nPocket (T)\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you all notice, the arrivals of paupiette and zarb were cancelled due to their \"ghost mod\" .Swarm and whiteman were moved to the  hall of fame for the same reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I wanted to make this to know the real active nB) team and to free some spots as i said. I don\'t want us to be inactive which is not the case at all, but i don\'t want to react too late.I hope there won\'t cause any fight but i\'m pretty sure it will be ok, the whole team will remain united in spite of all the little fights that can happen (it\'s a sentence i tried to find to justify that gif!! xD)\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"http://uppix.net/e/6/d/4c84021e5050e6199a3a45d1b66d9.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>','2011-06-13 11:05:25'),(11,2,1,'A Teamspeak for the whole team','<p><img src=\"http://t2.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTTjzeFWluGsgLB9_iQyGM8niZ1P2F9GCb5q6mU-6F01HX4RytN\" alt=\"\" /> <h3>A nB) Server</h3><p>\r\n\r\n<p> Thanks to nB)ALundra, we have access to a teamspeak server, i would like us to join that server to create even more team spirit in the team and well, to discuss and taunt online. For the good health of anybody , i\'ll try to cut my micro during wars so that everybody won\'t see how i can be anxious during those events :p </p>\r\n\r\n<p> On top of that, i would like you to be connected during wars, because it will make admin\'s life easier, not obliged to msg 15 people at the same time during event will help us to breathe </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teamspeak server: 91.191.159.207:9969\r\nFor the password, you just have to ask me in game so that you can bookmark the server to join easily next time.</p>','2011-06-15 09:17:18'),(12,2,1,'Pgleague nB vs Blast , unstoppable?','<h3><img src=\"http://nsa15.casimages.com/img/2010/04/07/100407110712744834.gif\" alt=\"\" /></h3>\r\n\r\n<p> This week was the second clanwar vs the well known Blast team , a really good team from D1 pandaria. We have to stress that our line up is more international than ours, and as pgleague only authorize one stranger, they had to put more french but still talented players such as fawzi.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:47}</div></p>\r\n<p> A really nice war from the whole team, first of all Pepem managed to beat ilak with a large score of 2-0 which put us in a nice situation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately , sweety lost his PvP 0-2 and the score went back to draw 1-1.</p>\r\n<p>But at the same time, Rasmuth managed to defeat the stronger player from the opponent\'s lineup: Jack , 2 really nice games i advise you to see.</p>\r\n<p>Bouh then,  had to fight vs fawzy and managed to win his game, gg to him, that\'s quite a nice performance!\r\nAt this moment the win is for us : 3-1.</p>\r\n<p>The 2v2 was quite important too, that was the first time pepem and pocket could express themselves in an official war, fighting blast was not the best for a start but they won 2-0. A really nice beginning.</p>\r\n<p>A really nice start for nB) with a 8-2 total score for the first wars. But the next war will be really hard, vs the gay team of Haddes!! They \'re doing an excellent job in pgleague and we\'ll have to take care.</p>','2011-06-15 09:30:40'),(13,2,1,'Pgleague day 3 nB vs SN','<img src=\"http://media.bo-pb.com/site/biarritz/no_match.gif\" alt=\"\" /><h3>nB vs SN-</h3>\r\n<p> Pour ce 3Ã¨me jour de pgleague, nous affrontions la belle Ã©quipe SN et voyons ce que cela a donnÃ©:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:49}</div>\r\n<p> VoilÃ  donc une rÃ©elle contre performance par rapport au dÃ©but de la saison.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Pepem perd 2-0 contre nam qui avait trÃ¨s bien prÃ©parÃ© son match et cela s\'est vu, bravo Ã  lui. </p>\r\n\r\n<p> Rasmuth perdra assez rapidement sur le mÃªme score face Ã  un izno au dessus , on aurait pu penser que notre grec prÃ©fÃ©rÃ© aurait Ã©tÃ© capable de soutenir la comparaison, malheureusement ce ne fut pas le cas </p>\r\n\r\n<p> Tartiflette aura perdu 2-1 face Ã  Metzi, mais je tiens Ã  le fÃ©liciter de sa trÃ¨s bonne prestation, il nous a montrÃ© des talents de macro qui je l\'espÃ¨re l\'inciteront Ã  avoir plus confiance et Ã  continuer de jouer un jeu solide comme il l\'a fait sur ce match. </p>\r\n\r\n<p> Bouh aura rendu une copie quasi parfaite face Ã  renzan, particuliÃ¨rement dans le dernier match oÃ¹ il aura tentÃ© une tactique Ã  laquelle je n\'Ã©tais pas habituÃ© venant de lui. C\'est un petit peu ce qui manque Ã  quelques nB), Bouh a plus d\'une corde Ã  son arc et commence Ã  disposer d\'un panel de techniques intÃ©ressantes, un peu Ã  la maniÃ¨re de tartiflette . Ce sera sans nul doute un atout dans les bo3 Ã  venir. Bravo.</p>\r\n\r\nFinalement pocket et pepem n\'ont pas rÃ©ussi Ã  accrocher la team izno renzan, mais en tenant compte du peu d\'entrainement dont ils ont bÃ©nÃ©ficiÃ© , je reste particuliÃ¨rement confiant pour la suite. A bientÃ´t pour un prochain cw et bravo pour les SN qui Ã©taient tout simplement mieux prÃ©parÃ©s .\r\n\r\nJe ne leur tiendrai pas rigueur de cette violente dÃ©faite. <img src=\"http://gifs.humour.free.fr/zidanegifs/bv000023.gif\" alt=\"\" />','2011-06-21 23:09:07'),(14,9,1,'PGL day4:  nB) 4-1 CsT','Hey there,\r\n<p>Short news about 4th playday of PG league. We played against CsT, a team which played in 1st division in pandaria. We had to win this important CW to stay in race for playoffs.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Here are the results: </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:50}</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, we managed to take 4 BO3 in this CW which is really a great result since sN- lost against BLAST which set us in 1st place with the same amount of points that sN-.\r\nOnly the freeloser Sweety lost his BO3 against an imba terran while Pepem managed to win a ZvZ versus a really good player.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover we are now assured to play the playoffs because we are currently 1-1 versus eX in last playday which means we can\'t get caught back by them even if we lose the remaining BO3.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>So good job guys, keep training, I guess we will have a chance to take a revenge versus Soleil Noir in playoffs !</p>','2011-07-04 00:55:22'),(15,9,1,'Welcome to Ninja in the team!','Fzero told us the good news last night before going on holidays that we had a new comer in the team!\r\n\r\n<p>Most of us have already played with him in CG recently, Ninja is a good french Terran player who is always ready for CG and improve his level.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>I don\'t know him very well, so I can\'t really speak about him but I guess Fzero will complete this news if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think he is a BW player who also played for aAa at the beginning of SC2. His great experience will definately help us to improve and it\'s also a new Terran in the active team, which is a good thing since there were only Tartiflette and MttN in the competitive roster. </p>\r\n<p>Welcome to Ninja!</p>','2011-07-05 16:22:51'),(16,9,1,'Last playday of PGL !','<h3>Already the last playday of regular season of PG League.</h3>\r\n<p>We were facing eXtensive! a strong team composed by really good players who are well known on WC3. Even if they are not training as hard as we do on SC2, they are very good.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe managed to take the win in the CW with a 3-2 score which is the best way to finish the season: winning!</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:52}</div>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, I played the 2v2 with Pepem since PocKeT weren\'t available and I was quite surprised that we won. Indeed it was the very first time we played together as 2v2 but hopefully the legendary 8 pool of Pepem did the job to bring us the win!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So gg all for this playday and this season, we did a really nice record with 4-1 only losing versus sN-.\r\nThis sets us as second just one point behind sN- which means we\'ll play the playoffs !</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We\'ll face the BLAST team in semi final so keep training, winning this next CW would lead us in final which would be a great result!</p>','2011-07-07 22:48:50'),(17,9,1,'PGL: Playoffs !','<p>As you know, we qualified for the playoffs of PG League finishing second of 1st division.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>As you can see there <a href=\"www.pgleague.fr/?Page=news_view&id=47\">pg league news</a> we\'ll play versus BLAST in semi final. The CW will be on Wednesday, July 13th so I hope we\'ll have a lot of people here to support us!</p> \r\n\r\n<p>As it\'s an important CW, it would be nice to prepare for it in order to reach the final! So we need to know as soon as possible if Muth, Pepem, Bouh, Tartiflette, PocKeT and I are available next tuesday to play the CW. </p>','2011-07-07 22:58:04'),(18,7,1,'[Upd] NBIT : Maps and Veto','<p>\r\n	Hello everyone! Today we are glad to announce that the <strong>Nuit Blanche Inside Tournament</strong> is ready to start !</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It will last the whole summer and will see all nB) try to become the true Champion of the team! Auyalolz and BsK are our plus one since they spend time on the channel Clan nB).<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Here are the groups :<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Group 1<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	2-1 (5-3) <img alt=\"(P)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Picon_small.png\" />Ayuyalolz<br />\r\n	1-0 (2-1) <img alt=\"(P)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Picon_small.png\" />Sweety<br />\r\n	0-1 (1-2) <img alt=\"(P)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Picon_small.png\" />Hane<br />\r\n	0-1 (0-2) <img alt=\"(Z)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Zicon_small.png\" />BsK<br />\r\n	0-0 (0-0) <img alt=\"(Z)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Zicon_small.png\" />Pepem<br />\r\n	0-0 (0-0) <img alt=\"(T)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Ticon_small.png\" />Ninja<br />\r\n	0-0 (0-0) Kura</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Group 2<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	2-1 (4-3) <img alt=\"(T)(Z)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Ticon_small.png\" />loveeyes<br />\r\n	2-2 (5-5) <img alt=\"(Z)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Zicon_small.png\" />Heero<br />\r\n	1-0 (2-1) <img alt=\"(P)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Picon_small.png\" />Bouh<br />\r\n	0-2 (2-4) <img alt=\"(Z)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Zicon_small.png\" />Beerwithme<br />\r\n	1-1 (3-1) <img alt=\"(P)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Picon_small.png\" />Muth<br />\r\n	0-0 (0-0) <img alt=\"(T)\" src=\"http://www.teamliquid.net/tlpd/images/Ticon_small.png\" />Tartiflette</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	0-0 (0-0) Lio<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	If anyone is not in the list and would like to be, post a comment, groups can be updated.<br />\r\n	All matchs are played in Bo3, the top 4 goes to the double bracket.<br />\r\n	We will try to stream some games if it will possible.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	You can play your matchs when you want, try not to delay them too much : 1 match per week would be perfect.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Gl Hf Map pool is : Terminus, taldarim, shakuras, esl metalo, esl ST, XNC, testbug, Crevasse, neo enigma.<br />\r\n	Each player veto two maps , then pick one map, then veto 1 maps, the remaining will be played if needed</p>','2011-07-09 13:40:19'),(19,9,1,'PGL: Playoffs nB) 3-2 BLAST','<p>As you know today we played the semi final of PGL playoffs and we played against BLAST. Here comes a short summary of the CW.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At first, Pepem played versus Indy, a very strong polish protoss, on monday. He managed to take a really important point winning his Bo3 versus I guess their best player</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, Bouh lost his PvP versus kimo and CW was at 1-1. Unfortunately, both teams had away players so we played the 2v2 with Pepem and I. We managed to win the first map and the BLAST admin decided to forfeit the 2v2 so we came to 2-1 in the CW.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since Diallo was not connected, Ilak replaced him to play against me and I lost 2-0 my PvP as Bouh showed me how to do !</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was 2-2 in the CW, only MuTh versus Crappy to play... but MuTh was not here ! \r\nHopefully, Bouh called HeeRo who instantly came to replace MuTh !</p> \r\n<p>\r\nThe last game was played and HeeRo managed to win 2-0 bringing us the point of the victory which leads us into final!! </p>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:53}</div>\r\n<p>GG all ! Especially HeeRo who is the hero of the CW bringing us the qualification to final !!! \r\nAs you can see, our protoss still suck hard, hopefully zergs are here to earn some points!</p>','2011-07-14 03:58:32'),(20,9,1,'PGL: Weee areee the champioooooonss !','<h3>Tonight we played the final of PG League!</h3>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.pgleague.fr/?Page=news_view&id=53\">here is the news</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>After one the best CW with really nice BO3 and wonderful games by both team, we managed to win the final of PGLeague 3-2 against sN- !</p> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">{war:54}</div>\r\n\r\n<p>There were a friendly ambiance with the FoX streamers who made us live the CW in perfect way.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nGG to the players for this amazing CW!\r\nGG to all the nB) members for this season!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to the PGL staff for their work.\r\nThanks to the FoX Team for the stream.\r\nAnd thanks everyone who supported us!</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI guess Fzero will be proud of us and proud of winning against his friend HaddeS !</p>','2011-07-18 01:27:48'),(21,1,1,'New SC2CL season to begin soon !','<img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/pics/82973.gif\" alt=\"SC2CL.com\" />\r\n<p>Yep we won our first league title of SC2, but we aren\'t in holidays yet !</p>\r\n<p>Next week-end will begin the new SC2CL season, the third one. We\'ll compete in the same <strong>3b division</strong>.</p>\r\n<h2>Here are our opponents and clan war dates (it\'s still sundays at 19.00) :</h2>\r\n24/07 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/deutschland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> NWO<br />\r\n31/07 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/deutschland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> oOa<br />\r\n07/08 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/italien.gif\" alt=\"\" /> OSC<br />\r\n14/08 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/spanien.gif\" alt=\"\" /> GIANTS!<br />\r\n28/08 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/italien.gif\" alt=\"\" /> Team Redbyte Italia<br />\r\n04/09 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/deutschland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> DRUCKWELLE<br />\r\n11/09 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/deutschland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> causeWEcan<br />\r\n18/09 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/deutschland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> logiX<br />\r\n25/09 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/russland.gif\" alt=\"\" /> 7x team<br />\r\n02/10 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/norwegen.gif\" alt=\"\" /> aGitated<br />\r\n09/10 : <img src=\"http://ingame.ingame.de/news/flaggen/litauen.gif\" alt=\"\" /> Figure05<br />\r\n\r\n<p>As u can see, there are many international teams from all over europe, and the schedule is really long. I guess it\'ll be really fun to play.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Objectives ? Who is involved ?</h3>\r\n<p>As usual, SC2CL is our \"clan war laboratory\", it\'s dedicated to players who want to train and who don\'t have a roster spot in Pandaria or PGLeague.<br />Usual players (Pepem, MuTh, Bouh, and others) can play in it to if they want to play and to train a bit. The goal is to involve everyone and to play as a complete team, opposed to Pandaria / PGLeague where our goal is a bit to promote the team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our objective is to maintain ourselves in division 3, so, be prepared ! We need to be in a good division in SC2CL for this training to be efficient.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Here is the map pool :</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>GSL Bel\'Shir Beach</li>\r\n<li>SC2CL - Shakuras Plateau</li>\r\n<li>SC2Cl - Metalopolis</li>\r\n<li>Xel\'Naga Caverns</li>\r\n<li>GSTL GSL Terminus Re</li>\r\n<li>SC2CL - Tal Darim Altar </li>\r\n<li>SC2CL Shattered Temple</li>\r\n<li>GSL Crevasse</li>\r\n<li>GSL Crossfire SE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>2on2</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tempest</li>\r\n<li>Scorched Haven</li>\r\n<li>Monlyth Ridge</li>\r\n<li>Khaydarin Depths</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>I\'m your main admin for this league, so don\'t hesitate to tell me whenever you want to play in it. New players or older ones who didn\'t subscribed SC2CL.com yet, please do it before the end of the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cheers,<br />AlepH</p>','2011-07-18 10:16:07'),(23,1,1,'PGL: Pepem elected MVP','<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://i200.photobucket.com/albums/aa38/NRHS07/Fantasy%20Football/Trophy-MVP.jpg\" style=\"width:110px; float:left; margin-right: 10px;\" />\r\n<p>\r\n	A little news to congratulate <span class=\"player-data\">{player:Pepem}</span> .<br />\r\n	As PGLeague revealed their trophies yesterday, they chose Pepem as MVP of the league.<br />\r\n	He did really well indeed, only loosing to nAm in the first clan war we played against sN-, winning against iZno, Indy, Netsky, Naijik, Shade, Ilak and Lycosa.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	So gg to him.. and to all of us again ; )<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	[edit] And a tiny gg to <span class=\"player-data\">{player:Bouh} </span>for being in the &quot;the could have been MVP&quot; list. Could have, but eventually not :p</p>\r\n<div class=\"spacer\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>','2011-07-19 15:39:12'),(24,1,1,'He\'s back','<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wootgaming.unblog.fr/files/2009/12/grinch.jpg\" style=\"height: 127px; width: 110px; float: left; margin-right: 5px;\" />\r\n<p>There was a rumor. People where whispering. But here is the truth. He&#39;s back ! <br />\r\nWe are really, truely happy to welcome back {player:EternalOne} aKa Clafter.\r\n<br />\r\nHe was the missing part of our &quot;15-active guyz&quot; objective for our roster.<br />\r\nIf you check our<a href=\"http://www.clan-nuitblanche.org/team/1/show\"> active roster page</a>, you&#39;ll see how great our line up now look like. We now have a really strong core of players allowing us to make rotation on Clan Wars based on needs and availability.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd with Clafter back, we&#39;ll now have 3 really good 2on2 teams with {player:Pepem} +&nbsp;<span class=\"player-data\">{player:PocKeT}</span><span class=\"player-data\">, {player:EternalOne} +&nbsp;</span><span class=\"player-data\">{player:loveeyes},&nbsp;</span><span class=\"player-data\">{player:Sweety} +&nbsp;</span><span class=\"player-data\">{player:Tartiflette}, not mentionning&nbsp;</span><span class=\"player-data\">{player:MttN} or&nbsp;</span><span class=\"player-data\">{player:mYst} two really good 2on2 players.</span><br />\r\nHope u like it,<br />\r\nCheers and stay tuned !</p>','2011-07-22 18:25:36'),(25,2,1,'Need games for few money?','<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.intkeys.com\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.thegamersblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/inkeyslogo.png\" style=\"width: 274px; height: 114px;\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Intkeys is a really nice website in which you can find the last games for nearly nothing and it&#39;s totally legal. I explain you how it works:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	First of all you buy the CD Key on the website, then you are allowed on steam for example to download the entire game since you possess an official CD key.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here is a short list of what you can find on this site:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.intkeys.com\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/873082intkeys.gif\" style=\"width: 505px; height: 656px;\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>REDUCTION CODE : d14cha91nx</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This code will allow you to have a 5% reduction on your next buy.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This site can turn into a partner for us if things go well so don&#39;t underestimate that news and if you&#39;re happy of your experience on that site, plz post it as a comment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I remind you the site : www.intkeys.com</p>','2011-07-24 12:54:24'),(26,7,1,'Welcome !','<p>\r\n	&nbsp;We are glad to announce a new member in the team !</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Indeed the French <img class=\"race-icon\" src=\"/bundles/ihqsnuitblanche/images/ico/zerg_icon.png\" /> BsK is now part of the team. Most of you&nbsp; know him since he spends a lot of time on the channel.&nbsp; He often takes part in competitions, both French and international. He qualified for the final of the starcraft2france tournament last month ofter goes far in other ones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can watch some of his replays on the website against strong players</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	So welcome him warmly !</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2011-07-24 18:02:04'),(27,1,1,'SC2CL S.3 : Week 1 result','<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://blogdwich.fr/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/vader-fail.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; width: 100px; height: 84px\" />A nice result for our first clan war of SC2CL s.3 !<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	We lost it 0-4 (last games for Raizou later) in a quite funky way. There really nothing to say... SC2CL is open to every players of the roster, and with a very different line up from our usual ones.</p>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	{war:55}</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	It&#39;s a good way to see that any &quot;B line up&quot; is a bit far from our &quot;A line up&quot; actually. We need more training ! Anyway, Svampis is a new ancient, love comes back from long internet holidays, raizou is on perpetual holidays so... it&#39;s really undertstandable too.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Anyway, we&#39;ll need better results to maintain in division 3. We&#39;ll maybe get a &quot;mix&quot; next clan war of &quot;usual line up players&quot; and other ones. It&#39;ll maybe be a better way to make everyone involved in more wars with a more standard approach.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Everyone, keep training, maybe we won PGL but there is many work left on the table ! We&#39;ve got really good players, but we must improve all together as a team ; )</p>','2011-07-24 23:23:35'),(28,2,1,'Creation of the INTKEYS nB) Cup','<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.intkeys.com\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.thegamersblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/inkeyslogo.png\" style=\"width: 274px; height: 114px;\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A good news for the nB) team, since we found a sponsor for a competition nB) Team will organize:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	That site will provide us a game for each tourney we make with the condition we make them known. I remind you that this site is really cool because it allows us to buy CD Keys that work on Steam for nearly nothing.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	That nB) Cup won&#39;t start before september i guess because we would like to host it on nB website in order to make him more visited and to be more efficient for our sponsor.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If everything works good, we can hope a lan sponsoring, it&#39;s up to us to make a good work on that .</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For those interested to buy a game : the usual reduction code: <strong>d14cha91nx</strong></p>','2011-07-27 13:27:09'),(29,4,1,'I AM BACK','<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cigalemistralavande.c.i.pic.centerblog.net/1plbmy4y.gif\" style=\"width: 171px; height: 171px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It deserves at least one news no?</p>','2011-08-01 02:21:05'),(30,2,1,'SC2CL s.3 - Day 3- SyS','<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://t0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQUqzsww9Udv3DJddBx1zdIWB_aGc3CZval3vBfcQDVHeDKEfS3pQ\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 159px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here is how it worked:</p>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	{war:56}</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	As you all can see it was tense, Sweety lost the first game and had to forfeit, Heero lost 1-2 again (hope he will win 2-1 next wars) .</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	A great job by BsK who managed to win his first clanwar for the team against a good T , he had to give up a game thanks to a marauders and hellions push but his mapping allowed him to spot the same technique on third game and he could counter well , nice games.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	And the hero of the war is Loveeyes with 2 points like old times, a 2-0 game in both 1v1 and 2v2 and 2 points for the team. It seems that Z fits him well . We can notice the return of our 2v2 gosu team Loveeyes + Clafter who did well for their come back .</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	GG to all and see you next week for next war (and i hope it will be streamed!)</div>','2011-08-01 13:09:30'),(31,2,1,'SC2Gears program','<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://sites.google.com/site/sc2gears/_/rsrc/1282206924789/config/5d9f5cae23acbc84.png\" style=\"width: 351px; height: 48px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is a really interesting SC2 tool i wanted to talk you about (thanks to BsK for making me discover it) . It&#39;s a tool in which you can analize any rep and it will give you some really interesting stats and graphs. You&#39;ll tell me that not so different from bnet but it&#39;s false.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In fact there&#39;s a multi reps analizing function which will gather all the informations from all your reps together . You can also gather informations from all opponents you faced on ladder or cg .</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	There is probably many other things to discover so i advise you to go there to dl the prog which seems to have a french translation:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://sites.google.com/site/sc2gears/\">http://sites.google.com/site/sc2gears/</a></p>','2011-08-01 14:04:21'),(32,12,1,'Wanna Be a PGM?','<p>\r\n	http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wtGCuZgZ8YY<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	:D</p>','2011-08-03 12:40:43'),(33,1,2,'ChiXi 2nd of Bunny League','<p>\r\n	A small news to congratulate <span class=\"player-data\">{player:ChiXi}</span> for her <strong>2nd place</strong> in the second edition of the bunny league.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	She only lost to <strong>DaSakura</strong>, a Canadian lady, winning versus a very good american girl in semi-final, <strong>flo</strong>, who won some editions of the ESL Female Cups.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.nationalesl.com/us/sc2/ironlady/bunnycup2/#/us/sc2/ironlady/bunnycup2/rankings/\">Here</a> is a complete recap of the bracket.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Gratz ChiXi, let&#39;s hope <span class=\"player-data\">{player:Still}</span> &amp; <span class=\"player-data\">{player:Milla}</span> will follow the way for the next editions of this cup ; )</p>','2011-08-07 19:39:17'),(34,2,1,'SC2CL s.3 - Day 3- oOa','<p>\r\n	Once again we had to fight the oOa team this season and let&#39;s see how it went:</p>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	{war:57}</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	As you can see, it&#39;s the first victory of svampis, with a good &quot;sunken attack &quot; in the first game and a nice use of infests in the last one, a good ZvZ.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	Heero has some difficulties to bring some points and lost to the good player Sauron, we wish him best luck for the future.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	Bouh and Muth won easily their games so, it&#39;s just a gg, they prove they are good players from the A line up.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	And to finish, a team i had to build for the last 2v2 game: Heero+ clafter.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	I don&#39;t like to build such inapropriate 22 teams and i really thank both players for playing. I hope one of our full 22 team will be available for next war.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	I remind you all that even if SC2CL is less &quot;entertaining&quot; for many members, we, admins, still have to manage it . So please help us and don&#39;t force us to find players 1 hour before the war because i admit i was fed up with it.</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"news-war\">\r\n	Anyway , good result, it&#39;s our second win in a row in SC2CL, let&#39;s continue.</div>','2011-08-08 11:53:09'),(35,2,1,'Creation of nB) team on Wannawar','<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://t1.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQPDaSwusz5_4ij8rSGY-NmkfkGk4GeyTHkXRNWt334rmfcplAp\" style=\"width: 100px; height: 160px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A small&nbsp; news to announce the creation of the team on the Wannawar website, this will allow to organize tourneys and above all to subscribe to nB team if you do some tourneys etc..</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I think it will help to make the team known.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Plz don&#39;t forget to join the team , or at least , to ask for joining it.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Petite news pour annoncer la cr&eacute;ation du clan nB) sur wannawar. Cela permettra aux joueurs participant aux divers tournois d&#39;arborer le beau logo nB) et ainsi permettre de mieux nous faire conna&icirc;tre.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	N&#39;oubliez pas de join, bande de moules!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2011-08-09 11:35:21');
